{
  "stem": "9701.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was actually a list of people who were going to be deported to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I looked through that list, even though that was not what I was actually looking for as far as my work was concerned.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I found my father's name on that list.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The list was dated January 1942, but I discounted it, because I still heard from my father as late as August 9th, 1942.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so I-- I don't know whether that list really was later on used when my father was deported.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That I don't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But I just discounted it at that time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I think-- you know, I discounted a whole lot of things that should have told me what happened to my parents, because I just could not accept that.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] When-- I had the opportunity sometimes when I was in Nuremberg to sit in on the court sessions, especially the trial of the doctors who performed the medical experiments.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I remember one young woman who had been experimented on who had to be carried into the court room because she could no longer walk.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The experiment that was conducted on her was a rusty knife had been used to cut open the fleshy part in the lower part of both of her legs and some foreign objects had been inserted, like rusty nail, dirt, or whatever.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And then it was sewn up again.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And the doctor, a woman who performed this experiment, woman by the name of Herta, H-E-R-T-A, Oberheuser, O-B-E-R-H-A-U-S-E-R, who was on trial and sitting in the docket, had performed this experiment on this young woman.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Most of the people who had this-- this kind of experiment conducted on them did not survive.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
